What is the Date of Event? <image 1> 

A. 5/19
B. 5/18
C. 5/17
D. 5/20

To determine the date of the event, we need to follow the timeline provided in the image. Here is the timeline:

1. 5/12 - 52 year old male admitted to oncology unit for chemotherapy with port in place
2. 5/17 - patient has ANC of 200 cells/mm³
3. 5/19 - patient has 2 blood cultures positive for Enterobacter cloacae
4. 5/21 - patient has total WBC of 150 cells/mm³; no other source of infection identified
5. 5/25 - patient discharged

The event that occurred on 5/19 is when the patient had 2 blood cultures positive for Enterobacter cloacae. Therefore, the correct answer is:

A. 5/19
